text: Yet Soo War Way Lee (1853 Tungkun, Guangdong, China – 21 August 1909 Adelaide, South Australia, Australia) was a Chinese-Australian merchant. Lee was a leader of the South Australian Chinese community who advocated for the rights of Chinese residents of Australia.Uncovering the remarkable Way Lee, (September 2009), UniSANews.
